        <abstract>
            <p>CD will pay for the American trip if it takes place.</p>
            <p>Asks whether FD can help him understand the eyes of cephalopods; is the structure the same as in the Vertebrata and are the parts developed from homologous layers of skin?</p>
            <p>Has been pleased by a recent review.</p> 
<p>Postscript: Is thinking of a cheap edition of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> [1872] in which he hopes to answer St George Mivart’s criticisms.</p>
            <p>Asks FD whether he can get some references to good papers on cephalapod eyes.</p>
        </abstract>
